  "body": "The beacon node securing to beacon networks is not stable enough. Latest docker image has been pulled down to run the beacon node locally, after a few minutes` execution, the beacon node could not execute state transition any more with unexpected reason. The validator`s behaviour was also impact by this fault. Here is some log output when error appeared:\r\n```\r\ntime=\"2019-05-24 02:29:49\" level=info msg=\"Chain head block and state updated\" headRoot=0x721d14c6dabbedf7d8293524 headSlot=21718 prefix=blockchain stateSlot=21718\r\ntime=\"2019-05-24 02:29:55\" level=info msg=\"Executing state transition\" prefix=blockchain slotNumber=21719\r\ntime=\"2019-05-24 02:29:55\" level=info msg=\"Block attestations\" attestationsInBlock=64 prefix=\"core/state\"\r\ntime=\"2019-05-24 02:29:55\" level=info msg=\"Block deposits\" depositsInBlock=0 prefix=\"core/state\"\r\ntime=\"2019-05-24 02:29:55\" level=error msg=\"Could not process beacon block: block failed processing: could not process epoch: bitfield is unable to be verified\" prefix=regular-sync\r\ntime=\"2019-05-24 02:29:58\" level=info msg=\"Executing state transition\" prefix=blockchain slotNumber=21719\r\ntime=\"2019-05-24 02:29:58\" level=info msg=\"Block attestations\" attestationsInBlock=64 prefix=\"core/state\"\r\ntime=\"2019-05-24 02:29:58\" level=info msg=\"Block deposits\" depositsInBlock=0 prefix=\"core/state\"\r\n```\r\nThe full docker log could be referred as below:\r\n[beacon0524.log](https://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/files/3214934/beacon0524.log)\r\n",
